<div class="legal-page about-page">
  <h1>About Meme Explorer</h1>
  
  <section class="hero-section">
    <p class="tagline">Discover the best memes from Reddit, curated with taste.</p>
  </section>
  
  <section>
    <h2>🎯 Our Mission</h2>
    <p>Meme Explorer is dedicated to bringing you the finest selection of memes from Reddit's vast ecosystem. We believe that humor brings people together, and great memes deserve to be discovered, appreciated, and shared.</p>
    <p>Our platform combines cutting-edge curation algorithms with human taste to surface the most entertaining, wholesome, and culturally relevant memes from across Reddit's diverse communities.</p>
  </section>
  
  <section>
    <h2>✨ What We Offer</h2>
    <ul class="feature-list">
      <li><strong>Curated Collections:</strong> Carefully organized meme categories including Funny, Wholesome, Self-Care, Dank, and more</li>
      <li><strong>Quality Filtering:</strong> Advanced algorithms ensure only the best content makes it to your feed</li>
      <li><strong>Personalization:</strong> Build your taste profile as you interact with content</li>
      <li><strong>Gamification:</strong> Track streaks, earn XP, level up, and compete on leaderboards</li>
      <li><strong>Social Features:</strong> Save favorites, like memes, and share with friends</li>
      <li><strong>Trending Discovery:</strong> See what's hot across Reddit in real-time</li>
      <li><strong>Random Exploration:</strong> Discover unexpected gems with our serendipity engine</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  
  <section>
    <h2>🏛️ The Criterion Collection Approach</h2>
    <p>Inspired by The Criterion Collection's approach to film curation, we treat memes as cultural artifacts worthy of thoughtful presentation. Each meme is:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Properly attributed to its original creator</li>
      <li>Contextualized within its subreddit community</li>
      <li>Evaluated for quality, humor, and cultural significance</li>
      <li>Presented with curatorial commentary when appropriate</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  
  <section>
    <h2>🔍 Content Sourcing</h2>
    <p>All memes on Meme Explorer are sourced from Reddit's public API. We respect the Reddit community and its creators by:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Attribution:</strong> Always linking back to original posts and crediting authors</li>
      <li><strong>Compliance:</strong> Following Reddit's API Terms of Service</li>
      <li><strong>Respect:</strong> Not monetizing content without proper permissions</li>
      <li><strong>Quality:</strong> Only featuring memes that meet our community standards</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Important:</strong> We are not affiliated with Reddit, Inc. We are an independent platform that aggregates publicly available content.</p>
  </section>
  
  <section>
    <h2>🛡️ Content Standards</h2>
    <p>We maintain high standards for content quality and appropriateness:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>✅ Family-friendly humor from wholesome subreddits</li>
      <li>✅ Creative and original meme formats</li>
      <li>✅ Cultural commentary and satirical content</li>
      <li>✅ Uplifting and positive messages</li>
      <li>❌ Hate speech or discriminatory content</li>
      <li>❌ Graphic violence or disturbing imagery</li>
      <li>❌ Explicit adult content</li>
      <li>❌ Harassment or bullying</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  
  <section>
    <h2>🎮 Gamification Features</h2>
    <p>We've built an engaging experience to make meme browsing more rewarding:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Daily Streaks:</strong> Visit daily to maintain your streak and earn bonus XP</li>
      <li><strong>Experience Points (XP):</strong> Earn XP by liking, saving, and sharing memes</li>
      <li><strong>Levels & Titles:</strong> Progress through levels from "Casual Browser" to "Meme Lord"</li>
      <li><strong>Leaderboards:</strong> Compete with other meme enthusiasts</li>
      <li><strong>Achievements:</strong> Unlock badges and milestones</li>
      <li><strong>Surprise Rewards:</strong> Discover random bonuses and special content</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  
  <section>
    <h2>💡 Technology</h2>
    <p>Meme Explorer is built with modern web technologies:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Backend:</strong> Ruby/Sinatra for fast, lightweight performance</li>
      <li><strong>Database:</strong> PostgreSQL for reliable data storage</li>
      <li><strong>Caching:</strong> Redis for lightning-fast content delivery</li>
      <li><strong>APIs:</strong> Reddit API integration with intelligent rate limiting</li>
      <li><strong>Frontend:</strong> Progressive enhancement with vanilla JavaScript</li>
      <li><strong>Design:</strong> Responsive, mobile-first interface with dark mode support</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  
  <section>
    <h2>🤝 Community Guidelines</h2>
    <p>Meme Explorer is a positive, welcoming space. We expect all users to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Respect other users and content creators</li>
      <li>Report inappropriate content</li>
      <li>Engage authentically (no gaming the system)</li>
      <li>Give credit where credit is due</li>
      <li>Spread joy, not hate</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  
  <section>
    <h2>📊 Privacy & Advertising</h2>
    <p>We take your privacy seriously:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>We only collect data necessary to provide our service</li>
      <li>We use Google AdSense for advertising (ads can be blocked)</li>
      <li>We never sell your personal information</li>
      <li>You control your data and can request deletion anytime</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Read our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> for complete details.</p>
  </section>
  
  <section>
    <h2>🚀 Future Plans</h2>
    <p>We're constantly improving Meme Explorer. Coming soon:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Mobile app (iOS & Android)</li>
      <li>User-generated collections</li>
      <li>Advanced filtering and search</li>
      <li>Social sharing improvements</li>
      <li>Community voting features</li>
      <li>Multi-platform content sources</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  
  <section>
    <h2>📞 Contact Us</h2>
    <p>We love hearing from our users! Get in touch:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>General Inquiries:</strong> <a href="mailto:hello@meme-explorer.com">hello@meme-explorer.com</a></li>
      <li><strong>Support:</strong> <a href="/contact">Contact Form</a></li>
      <li><strong>Feedback:</strong> Use the feedback button on any meme</li>
      <li><strong>DMCA/Copyright:</strong> <a href="/dmca">DMCA Policy</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  
  <section class="cta-section">
    <h2>Join the Community</h2>
    <p>Ready to discover amazing memes?</p>
    <div class="cta-buttons">
      <% if session[:user_id] %>
        <a href="/trending" class="btn-primary">Browse Memes</a>
      <% else %>
        <a href="/signup" class="btn-primary">Sign Up Free</a>
        <a href="/trending" class="btn-secondary">Browse as Guest</a>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <section class="acknowledgment">
    <p><strong>Acknowledgments:</strong> Thank you to the Reddit community and all the talented meme creators who make this platform possible. Special shout-out to our mascot inspiration: Tattoo Annie from The Simpsons! 😎</p>
  </section>
</div>

